## Overview

The MSD (Master Systems Display) system follows a **pipeline architecture** with clear stages:

```mermaid
graph LR
    Config[User Config] --> Process[Process & Validate]
    Process --> Model[Build Model]
    Model --> Init[Initialize Systems]
    Init --> Render[Render Overlays]
    Render --> Updates[Runtime Updates]
    
    style Config fill:#f0f0f0,stroke:#666
    style Process fill:#4d94ff,stroke:#0066cc
    style Model fill:#ff9900,stroke:#cc7700
    style Init fill:#4d94ff,stroke:#0066cc
    style Render fill:#ff9900,stroke:#cc7700
    style Updates fill:#00cc66,stroke:#009944
```

**Key Principles:**
- ✅ **Unidirectional data flow** - Config → Model → Render
- ✅ **Immutable models** - Models are rebuilt, not mutated
- ✅ **Reactive updates** - DataSource changes trigger re-renders
- ✅ **Separation of concerns** - Each stage has a single responsibility


