## Configuration Processing

### Pack Merging Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Config
    participant PM as PackMerger
    participant BuiltIn as Builtin Packs
    participant External as External Packs
    participant Merge as Merge Engine
    participant Prov as Provenance Tracker
    
    User->>PM: mergePacks(userConfig)
    
    PM->>BuiltIn: Load builtin packs
    BuiltIn-->>PM: builtin_themes, builtin_gallery
    
    PM->>PM: Check for external_packs in config
    
    alt Has external packs
        PM->>External: Fetch HTTP/HTTPS URLs
        External->>External: Validate pack structure
        External->>External: Check version compatibility
        External-->>PM: External pack data
    end
    
    PM->>Merge: processSinglePass(layers)
    
    loop For each pack layer
        Merge->>Prov: Track source & priority
        Merge->>Merge: Deep merge with overrides
        Merge->>Merge: Concatenate arrays (overlays, rules, etc.)
        Merge->>Merge: Merge objects (themes, style_presets, etc.)
    end
    
    Merge-->>PM: Merged configuration
    
    PM->>PM: Validate merged structure
    PM-->>User: { merged, provenance, timing }
```

### Configuration Layers

Packs are merged in priority order (highest priority last):

```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph "Layer 1: Builtin"
        BT[builtin_themes<br/>Themes, presets, templates]
        BG[builtin_gallery<br/>Sample overlays]
    end
    
    subgraph "Layer 2: External"
        EP1[External Pack 1<br/>Community pack]
        EP2[External Pack 2<br/>Custom pack]
    end
    
    subgraph "Layer 3: User"
        UC[User Config<br/>Final overrides]
    end
    
    BT --> Merge[Merge Engine]
    BG --> Merge
    EP1 --> Merge
    EP2 --> Merge
    UC --> Merge
    
    Merge --> Final[Final Config]
    
    style BT fill:#4d94ff,stroke:#0066cc
    style BG fill:#4d94ff,stroke:#0066cc
    style EP1 fill:#00cc66,stroke:#009944
    style EP2 fill:#00cc66,stroke:#009944
    style UC fill:#ff9900,stroke:#cc7700
    style Final fill:#f0f0f0,stroke:#666,stroke-width:3px
```

