## Systems Initialization

### Systems Manager Architecture

```mermaid
graph TB
    SM[Systems Manager<br/>Central Orchestrator]
    
    subgraph "Data Layer"
        DSM[DataSource Manager<br/>HA entity integration]
        TP[Template Processor<br/>Template resolution]
    end
    
    subgraph "Logic Layer"
        RE[Rules Engine<br/>Conditional logic]
        TM[Theme Manager<br/>Theme & defaults]
    end
    
    subgraph "Rendering Layer"
        AR[Advanced Renderer<br/>Main renderer]
        SR[Specialized Renderers<br/>Text, Button, Line, etc.]
    end
    
    subgraph "Support Systems"
        APM[Attachment Point Manager<br/>Anchor management]
        RC[Router Core<br/>Line routing]
        AnimReg[Animation Registry<br/>Animations]
        SRS[Style Resolver Service<br/>Style resolution]
    end
    
    SM --> DSM
    SM --> TP
    SM --> RE
    SM --> TM
    SM --> AR
    SM --> APM
    SM --> RC
    SM --> AnimReg
    SM --> SRS
    
    AR --> SR
    AR --> APM
    AR --> RC
    
    DSM --> TP
    TM --> SRS
    
    style SM fill:#ff9900,stroke:#cc7700,stroke-width:3px
    style AR fill:#ff9900,stroke:#cc7700,stroke-width:2px
    style DSM fill:#4d94ff,stroke:#0066cc,stroke-width:2px
```

### System Initialization Sequence

Each system is initialized in dependency order:

1. **ThemeManager** - Loads theme tokens and component defaults
2. **DataSourceManager** - Subscribes to Home Assistant entities
3. **TemplateProcessor** - Prepares template engine
4. **RulesEngine** - Parses rules and tracks dependencies
5. **StyleResolverService** - Initializes style resolution
6. **AttachmentPointManager** - Prepares anchor system
7. **RouterCore** - Initializes routing algorithms
8. **AnimationRegistry** - Registers animations
9. **AdvancedRenderer** - Creates rendering pipeline

