## Rendering Pipeline

### Render Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Trigger as Update Trigger
    participant Render as reRender()
    participant MB as ModelBuilder
    participant TM as ThemeManager
    participant TP as TemplateProcessor
    participant RE as RulesEngine
    participant SRS as StyleResolverService
    participant AR as AdvancedRenderer
    participant SR as Specialized Renderers
    participant DOM as SVG/DOM Output
    
    Trigger->>Render: Data change / Rule match / Manual
    
    Render->>MB: computeResolvedModel()
    
    MB->>MB: Start with base model
    MB->>TM: Get theme defaults
    TM-->>MB: Component defaults
    
    MB->>TP: Process templates
    TP->>TP: Resolve {datasource.id} refs
    TP->>TP: Evaluate HA {{ }} templates
    TP-->>MB: Resolved content
    
    MB->>RE: Evaluate rules
    RE->>RE: Check conditions
    RE->>RE: Apply matching rule styles
    RE-->>MB: Rule results
    
    MB->>SRS: Resolve all styles
    SRS->>SRS: 5-tier style resolution
    SRS->>SRS: Token resolution
    SRS-->>MB: Final styles
    
    MB-->>Render: resolvedModel
    
    Render->>AR: render(resolvedModel)
    
    loop For each overlay
        AR->>SR: Render specific overlay type
        SR->>SR: Create/update elements
        SR-->>AR: Rendered elements
    end
    
    AR->>DOM: Update SVG container
    AR->>DOM: Update HTML elements
    
    AR-->>Render: Render complete
```

### Overlay Rendering

```mermaid
graph LR
    Model[Resolved Model] --> AR[Advanced Renderer]
    
    AR --> Text[TextOverlayRenderer]
    AR --> Button[ButtonOverlayRenderer]
    AR --> Line[LineOverlayRenderer]
    AR --> Grid[StatusGridRenderer]
    AR --> Chart[ApexChartsOverlay]
    AR --> Sparkline[SparklineRenderer]
    
    Text --> SVG[SVG Container]
    Button --> SVG
    Line --> SVG
    Sparkline --> SVG
    
    Grid --> DOM[HTML Elements]
    Chart --> DOM
    
    style AR fill:#ff9900,stroke:#cc7700,stroke-width:2px
    style SVG fill:#f0f0f0,stroke:#666
    style DOM fill:#f0f0f0,stroke:#666
```

